<title ixia_locid="207" class="- topic/title ">[RC] taskbody: TiS Initializing Controller-0 [for main trunk]</title>
<rcbody class="- topic/body referable-content/body ">
        <taskbody id="taskbody_N10011_N1000E_N10001" class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
            <prereq id="prereq_N1002B_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="166" class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
                <p ixia_locid="169" class="- topic/p ">Before installing the software on the first controller, ensure
                    the following:</p>
                <ul id="ul_p5w_hwh_g4" class="- topic/ul ">
                    <li ixia_locid="172" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p ixia_locid="175" class="- topic/p ">The host meets the hardware requirements for a
                            controller.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li ixia_locid="90" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p ixia_locid="10" class="- topic/p ">You have terminal-server access to the host, so that you
                            can monitor messages during initialization.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li ixia_locid="178" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p ixia_locid="181" class="- topic/p ">The management, OAM, and optional PXE boot and
                            infrastructure networks are planned, set up, and connected.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li ixia_locid="91" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p ixia_locid="92" class="- topic/p ">All other hosts on the system are powered off.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li ixia_locid="93" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p ixia_locid="94" class="- topic/p ">You have reviewed the Release Notes for any additional
                            information pertaining to installation. </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </prereq>
            <steps id="all_steps" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
                <step id="power_on_host" ixia_locid="61" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd ixia_locid="62" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Power on the host to be configured as <nameliteral ixia_locid="184" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">controller-0</nameliteral>.</cmd>
                </step>
                <step id="configure_BIOS_for_boot" ixia_locid="11" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd ixia_locid="12" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Configure the host BIOS boot sequence to boot from a USB
                        removable storage device.</cmd>
                </step>
                <step id="insert_USB_flash_drive" ixia_locid="14" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd ixia_locid="15" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Insert the USB flash drive and boot the host.</cmd>
                    <stepresult ixia_locid="16" class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
                        <p ixia_locid="17" class="- topic/p ">The installer welcome screen appears.</p>
                        <fig id="fig_N10059_N10052_N1004B_N1003C_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="18" class="- topic/fig ">
                            <title ixia_locid="19" class="- topic/title ">HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Installer Welcome Screen</title>
                            <image href="jow1433084986736.image" id="image_yzn_skg_fs" ixia_locid="208" product="tis_not_small" placement="inline" class="- topic/image ">
                                <alt ixia_locid="209" class="- topic/alt ">TiS Installer screen (basic)</alt>
                            </image>
                            <image href="jow1404333487370.image" id="image_wvh_5kg_fs" ixia_locid="210" product="tis_small" placement="inline" class="- topic/image ">
                                <alt ixia_locid="211" class="- topic/alt ">TiS Installer screen with two-server configuration</alt>
                            </image>
                        </fig>
                    </stepresult>
                </step>
                <step id="select_installation_type" ixia_locid="21" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd ixia_locid="22" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the type of installation and the display device to
                        be used during initialization, and then press <uicontrol ixia_locid="23" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                    <info ixia_locid="145" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                        <p ixia_locid="205" product="tis_small" class="- topic/p ">To install a standalone controller, select from the
                            first group.</p>
                        <dl class="- topic/dl ">
                            <dlentry ixia_locid="187" class="- topic/dlentry ">
                                <dt ixia_locid="190" class="- topic/dt "><nameliteral ixia_locid="193" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Serial Controller
                                        Node Install</nameliteral> (default)</dt>
                                <dd ixia_locid="196" class="- topic/dd ">
                                    <p ixia_locid="185" class="- topic/p ">Installs the controller function on the
                                        host, using the serial port to display messages. You can
                                        monitor the port using the terminal server.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry ixia_locid="199" class="- topic/dlentry ">
                                <dt ixia_locid="164" class="- topic/dt "><nameliteral ixia_locid="170" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Graphics
                                        Controller Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd ixia_locid="201" class="- topic/dd ">
                                    <p ixia_locid="203" class="- topic/p ">Installs the controller function on the
                                        host, using graphics mode to display messages. This
                                        selection works with most console displays.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry ixia_locid="167" class="- topic/dlentry ">
                                <dt ixia_locid="179" class="- topic/dt "><nameliteral ixia_locid="173" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Graphics Text
                                        Controller Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd ixia_locid="176" class="- topic/dd ">
                                    <p ixia_locid="182" class="- topic/p ">Installs the controller function on the
                                        host, using text mode to display messages. This is a safe
                                        option for nodes that do not support graphics mode.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                        </dl>
                        <p ixia_locid="206" product="tis_small" class="- topic/p ">To install a minimal two-server configuration, in which
                            the controller and compute functions are implemented on a single host,
                            select from the second group.</p>
                        <dl product="tis_small" class="- topic/dl ">
                            <dlentry ixia_locid="188" class="- topic/dlentry ">
                                <dt ixia_locid="191" class="- topic/dt "><nameliteral ixia_locid="194" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Serial
                                        Controller+Compute Node Install</nameliteral> (default)</dt>
                                <dd ixia_locid="197" class="- topic/dd ">
                                    <p ixia_locid="186" class="- topic/p ">Installs controller and compute functions on
                                        the host, using the serial port to display messages. You can
                                        monitor the port using the terminal server.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry ixia_locid="200" class="- topic/dlentry ">
                                <dt ixia_locid="165" class="- topic/dt "><nameliteral ixia_locid="171" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Graphics
                                        Controller+Compute Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd ixia_locid="202" class="- topic/dd ">
                                    <p ixia_locid="204" class="- topic/p ">Installs controller and compute functions on
                                        the host, using graphics mode to display messages. This
                                        selection works with most console displays.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                            <dlentry ixia_locid="168" class="- topic/dlentry ">
                                <dt ixia_locid="180" class="- topic/dt "><nameliteral ixia_locid="174" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">Graphics Text
                                        Controller+Compute Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                <dd ixia_locid="177" class="- topic/dd ">
                                    <p ixia_locid="183" class="- topic/p ">Installs controller and compute functions on
                                        the host, using text mode to display messages. This is a
                                        safe option for nodes that do not support graphics mode.</p>
                                </dd>
                            </dlentry>
                        </dl>
                        <note id="note_N10167_N100C2_N100B3_N10058_N10012_N1000F_N10001" ixia_locid="212" class="- topic/note ">
                            <p ixia_locid="213" class="- topic/p "><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="214" translate="no" dir="ltr" class="- topic/draft-comment ">US62816 note added</draft-comment>The default rootfs device is
                                    <filepath ixia_locid="215" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath ">/dev/sda</filepath>. You can
                                optionally change this (or other parameters) by selecting the
                                installation mode, pressing the <uicontrol ixia_locid="216" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tab</uicontrol> key, modifying the command that appears, and
                                then pressing
                                <uicontrol ixia_locid="218" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol>.<codeblock ixia_locid="217" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock ">vmlinux rootwait console=ttyS0, 115200 root=LABEL=oe_iso_boot \
ngpt textinst serial ks=/mnt/install/source/ks.cfg boot_device=sda \
rootfs_device=sda initrd=initrd</codeblock></p>
                        </note>
                    </info>
                </step>
                <step id="monitor_initialization" ixia_locid="70" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd ixia_locid="71" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Monitor the initialization until it is complete.</cmd>
                    <info ixia_locid="72" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                        <p ixia_locid="73" class="- topic/p ">The installer initializes the target hard drive with the
                            HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade image. When initialization is complete, a reboot is
                            initiated on the host. </p>
                    </info>
                </step>
                <step id="remove_usb_flash_drive" ixia_locid="189" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd importance="high" ixia_locid="192" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Immediately remove the USB flash drive
                        from the host to ensure that the host reboots from the hard drive.</cmd>
                    <info ixia_locid="195" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                        <note id="note_N100C5_N100C2_N100B8_N1004B_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="67" type="caution" class="- topic/note ">
                            <p ixia_locid="198" class="- topic/p ">If the USB flash drive is still attached when the
                                host reboots, then unless the boot sequence has been configured to
                                prevent it, the host will boot from the USB flash drive again
                                instead of the hard drive.</p>
                        </note>
                        <p id="grub_displayed" ixia_locid="47" class="- topic/p "> After a few minutes, the host
                            reboots from the hard drive and displays the <wintitle ixia_locid="48" class="+ topic/keyword ui-d/wintitle ">GNU GRUB</wintitle> welcome screen.<fig id="fig_N100DB_N100D0_N100C9_N1003C_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="49" class="- topic/fig ">
                                <image alt="GNU GRUB screen" href="jow1404333488777.image" id="image_jb1_gfz_cn" ixia_locid="51" width="4in" placement="inline" class="- topic/image "/>
                            </fig></p>
                        <p ixia_locid="52" class="- topic/p ">After a brief delay, the system boots automatically into
                            the HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade image.</p>
                    </info>
                </step>
                <step id="log_in" ixia_locid="53" class="- topic/li task/step ">
                    <cmd ixia_locid="54" class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Log into the host as <userinput ixia_locid="55" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">wrsroot</userinput>, with password <userinput ixia_locid="56" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">wrsroot</userinput>.</cmd>
                    <info ixia_locid="140" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                        <note id="note_N1016E_N1016A_N10156_N1007D_N1002E_N10001" ixia_locid="149" class="- topic/note ">
                            <p ixia_locid="150" class="- topic/p ">Typed responses to password prompts are suppressed
                                and do not appear on the display.</p>
                        </note>
                        <p ixia_locid="142" class="- topic/p ">The first time you log in as <userinput ixia_locid="143" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">wrsroot</userinput>, you are required to change your password.</p>
                        <codeblock ixia_locid="151" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="152" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">Changing password for wrsroot.
(current) UNIX Password:</systemoutput></codeblock>
                        <p ixia_locid="153" class="- topic/p ">Enter the current password (<nameliteral ixia_locid="154" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">wrsroot</nameliteral>).</p>
                        <codeblock ixia_locid="155" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="156" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">New password:</systemoutput></codeblock>
                        <p ixia_locid="157" class="- topic/p ">Enter a new password for the <nameliteral ixia_locid="161" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">wrsroot </nameliteral>account.</p>
                        <codeblock ixia_locid="158" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="159" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">Retype new password:</systemoutput></codeblock>
                        <p ixia_locid="160" class="- topic/p ">Enter the new password again to confirm it.</p>
                    </info>
                </step>
            </steps>
            <result id="result_N10100_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="57" class="- topic/section task/result ">
                <p ixia_locid="58" class="- topic/p ">The host is now ready for configuration as <nameliteral ixia_locid="144" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">controller-0</nameliteral>.</p>
            </result>
        </taskbody>
    </rcbody>
